title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, we define what it means for a type to be <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> by induction:</fr:p><fr:ul><fr:li>a type is <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[-2]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> when it is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001H.xml"
addr="erct-001H"
title="Contractible type">contractible</fr:link>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>a type is <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> when it is a <fr:link
