href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>We proceed by induction on the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001F.xml"
addr="erct-001F"
title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  <fr:ol><fr:li>When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-2]]></fr:tex>, we recall from <fr:ref
addr="erct-001N"
href="erct-001N.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> that being <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001H.xml"
addr="erct-001H"
title="Contractible type">contractible</fr:link> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:li>
    <fr:li>When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-1]]></fr:tex>, we recall from <fr:ref
addr="erct-001O"
href="erct-001O.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> that
      being a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:li>
    <fr:li>For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n \geq  0]]></fr:tex>, we assume by induction that being <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link> to prove that being <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. In other words, we must show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathsf {isTruncated}\,  \mathopen {}\left \lparen n-1\right \rparen \mathclose {} \,A]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. By our inductive hypothesis, this is a dependent product of <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">propositions</fr:link> (<fr:ref
addr="erct-001B"
href="erct-001B.xml"
taxon="Corollary" />).</fr:li></fr:ol>
